    console.log('My script is initialized');
}
setTimeout(runMeFirst, 0);
console.log('Script loaded');
```

and the output would be in

```console
Script loaded
My script is initialized
```

If you don't use `setTimeout`, the order of logs will be sequential.

```javascript
